<%- include('../partials/tw-head') -%>
<body class="flex min-h-full flex-col bg-slate-50 text-slate-800 antialiased">
<%- include('../partials/tw-header') -%>
<main class="flex-1">
  <section class="border-b border-slate-200 bg-white py-12 sm:py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-faithGold">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-navy sm:text-4xl">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">Minimal collection, local-first products, and no surveillance-style growth tactics.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">Overview</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Faith Based Innovations, LLC builds desktop software intended to run primarily on your hardware. That posture shapes what we need from you online.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">What we collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">We collect what is needed to operate the business: licensing, commerce, support, and security—never “just in case.”</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">What we do not do</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">We do not build products around behavioral ad profiles. We do not sell attention as a product.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">Where data lives</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Application data is designed to remain on your device unless a feature explicitly uses an online service.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">Payments</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">When commerce is live, payment processing will use specialized providers named on this page.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">Your controls</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Local data can be removed by you directly. Account-related requests follow the process published with each product.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy">Updates</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Material policy changes receive a visible effective date and a concise summary of what changed.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
<%- include('../partials/tw-footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/tw-scripts') %>
</body>
</html>
